commit.message:
DISCONTINUED

I stopped working on virtus in 2015. Since then, there was no actual activity and no releases. I was holding off with any final decisions until I can be 100% sure that it's fine AND I can offer solid alternative solutions. Now with dry-types and dry-struct 1.0.0 released + dry-schema 1.0.0 release being around the corner, it's safe to say that virtus can be retired.

What this means is that I mark virtus project as discontinued and I encourage you to look into dry-rb libraries, if you haven't done it yet.

Thank you for using and supporting this ruby gem. It's been fun, now it's time to take another step forward 

Closes #386 

[ci skip]

README: Show correct result for `user.attributes`

Fixes #352. Shows that uninitialized attributes show up in `#attributes` as `nil`.

Merge pull request #343 from dslh/collection_value_coerced

Virtus::Attribute::Collection.value_coerced? override.

+ Virtus::Attribute::Collection.value_coerced?

Added override of `Virtus::Attribute.value_coerced?` to
`Virtus::Attribute::Collection`, which checks collection
members against the expected member type. Prevents e.g.
`Virtus::Attribute.build(Array[Integer]).value_coerced? %w{1 2 3}`
from returning `true`.
